All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
CancellationReportController
The CancellationReportController class is responsible for controlling the GUI for displaying cancellation reports.
ChatClient
This class overrides some of the methods defined in the abstract superclass in order to give more functionality to the client.
ChatIF
This interface implements the abstract method used to display objects onto the client or server UIs.
ClientController
This class constructs the UI for a chat client.
ClientUI
The main class for the client-side user interface.
CurClient
This class represents a client currently connected to the system.
DepartmentManagerApprovalController
This class controls the approval process for requests in the Department Manager interface.
DepartmentManagerHomePageController
This class controls the Department Manager Home Page interface.
EchoServer
This class overrides some of the methods in the abstract superclass in order to give more functionality to the server.
EditOrderController
This class controls the Edit Order interface.
EmailReciever
This class provides methods to check email responses for order confirmations or cancellations.
EmailSender
This class provides methods to send confirmation or waiting list update emails to visitors.
LoginController
This class controls the login process in the GUI.
LoginWithoutPasswordController
This class controls the login process without password (For visitor and guide) in the GUI.
MainFrameController
This class controls the main frame of the application.
Message
The Message class represents a message used for communication between different components of the park management system.
Message.ActionType
Enumeration representing different types of actions that can be performed.
MyFile
MyFile class represents a serializable object for storing file data.
mysqlConnection
The mysqlConnection class establishes a connection to a MySQL database and provides methods for verifying user logins and other functions.
Notification
The Notification class represents a notification related to an order in the park management system.
OpenGUI
Utility class for opening GUI windows.
Order
The Order class represents an order made by a visitor in the park management system.
Park
Represents a park with its attributes such as name, reserved capacity, total capacity, and maximum stay duration.
ParkManagerChangeCapacityController
This class controls the functionality of the Park Manager Change Capacity GUI.
ParkManagerHomePageController
This class controls the functionality of the Park Manager Home Page GUI.
Report
Represents a report with its attributes such as report type, park name, month, year, and details.
Request
The Request class represents a request for park information.
RunnableSql
This class implements the Runnable interface to perform various database operations in separate threads.
ServerInfoController
Controller class for managing server information GUI.
ServerUI
ServerUI class represents the user interface for managing the server.
ServicesHomePageController
This class controls the functionality of the Services Home Page GUI.
UsageVisitingReport
The UsageVisitingReport class represents a visiting report for usage statistics.
UsageVisitingReportController
This class controls the functionality of the Usage Visiting Report GUI.
User
The User class represents a user in the system.
VisitingReportController
This class controls the functionality of the Visiting Report GUI.
VisitorHomePageController
This class controls the functionality of the Visitor Home Page GUI.
WaitingListController
This class controls the functionality of the Waiting List GUI.
WaitingListEntry
The WaitingListEntry class represents an entry in the waiting list.
WorkerHomePageController
WorkerHomePageController is a controller class responsible for controlling the worker's home page UI.
